    <text type="letter">
        <body>

            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="upa.00057.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <note type="editorial" resp="#hg" place="top">Received Dec: 18th | H H G.</note>
                <note type="editorial" resp="#unk" place="top">Sprague Collection No 28</note>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden<ptr target="upa.00057_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1885-12-08" rend="right">Tuesday noon</date>
                    <date when="1885-12-08" rend="right">Dec: 8 '85</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friend<ptr target="upa.00057_n2"/></salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I think of you very often, &#38; cannot but trust your illness is less gloomy than
                Herbert states it&#8212;I know I have myself felt convinced several times during the
                last twelve or thirteen years of serious conditions &#38; fin&#225;l&#233;s that
                endurance has tided over&#8212;&#38; O I so hope that you will surmount
                all&#8212;&#38; that we may yet meet each other face to face.</p>
            <p>&#8212;I am middling well&#8212;the trouble in my eyesight (&#38; very annoying it was to my
                    <hi rend="underline">anchor'd</hi> condition) seems to have pass'd over&#8212;We
                are having extremely cold weather here, &#38; I do not get out of the
                house&#8212;but it is bright &#38; sunny as I look out&#8212;I wrote a card to
                Herbert three days ago, which I suppose he has rec'd&#8212;God's peace &#38; blessing
                to you, beloved friend&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
                <salute>with best love</salute>
            </closer>
